data.description: SUPER PRICE REDUCTION! INCOME PRODUCING POSSIBILITIES!  Lovely Vintage Home with all the charm you have been looking for with lovely outside living as well.  The home features 3 to 4 bedrooms with the primary bedroom on the main level.  Large room at the front of the home could be a great guest room or a perfect home office.  Every room in this house is large and could have multiple functions as bedrooms, offices, game rooms or more.  You will fall in love with the outside living starting with the huge front porch, original wrought iron railing and massive back deck.  The Lovely Serenity Garden is perfect for a quiet place to read, do yoga or for your children and pets.  The location is perfect just 20 minutes to Greenville, Easley or Anderson. Several great small towns nearby for activities such as Pickle Ball (brand new courts 10 minutes away), Playhouses, city parks and more.  The home was upgraded 5 years ago and has new Double HVAC, drop pane windows, vinyl siding, large deck and an even newer roof only 2 years old.  All 2" Custome Wood blinds remain in the home. The manicured yard and landscaping are always a showstopper in the neighborhood with one of the few tulip trees that has bloomed every spring. Super Low Utilities, see the attached Statements total for 2023 Gas and Power.  This home is located in a USDA eligible location please check the map. County of Greenville states, that tiny homes could be placed on this property for great Income Producing Possibilities!  For more explanation, please call the county for further discussion.
